INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the criteria used to determine when to launch an investigation into the whereabouts of a missing person.
EventItemMatterName: Criteria used to determine when to launch an investigation into the whereabouts of a missing person.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the issuance of building permits for areas in which a certified rezoning application is pending.
EventItemMatterName: Issuance of building permits for areas in which a certified rezoning application is pending.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to restricting the use of polystyrene foam food packaging.
EventItemMatterName: Restricting the use of polystyrene foam food packaging.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring mayoral agencies to issue monthly reports to the Council and the Public Advocate on compliance with the New York State Freedom of Information Law.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring mayoral agencies to issue monthly reports to the Council and the Public Advocate on compliance with the NYS Freedom of Information Law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to certain provisions of title 17 and to repeal subchapters 1 and 5 of chapter 3, relating to permits for the sale or transfer of milk and milk products and to medical records respectively.
EventItemMatterName: Permits for the sale or transfer of milk and milk products and to medical records respectively.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, to repeal and reenact section 17-337 relating to air quality standards for compressed air in underwater breathing tanks.
EventItemMatterName: Air quality standards for compressed air in underwater breathing tanks.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the definitions of terms that relate to the provision of information on child care services and to reporting on child care programs and to repeal certain provisions of the administrative code in relation thereto.
EventItemMatterName: Relating to reports regarding child care facilities.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to school nurses.
EventItemMatterName: School nurses.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to the removal or deactivation of fire department alarm boxes.
EventItemMatterName: Removal or deactivation of fire department alarm boxes.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to establishing fees for certain probation services.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing fees for certain probation services.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to increasing the wattage of electric lighting fixtures in certain public parts of multiple dwellings.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing the wattage of electric lighting fixtures in certain public parts of multiple dwellings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to training building inspectors.
EventItemMatterName: Training building inspectors.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Aging
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to permissible parking at senior centers.
EventItemMatterName: Permissible parking at senior centers.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Human Resources Administration to change its rules to allow Public Administrators to act as organizational friends.
EventItemMatterName: Human Resources Administration to change its rules to allow Public Administrators to act as organizational friends.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Mayor of the City of New York to examine how the City’s economic policies can be strengthened to address the disparate unemployment rate and joblessness of black New Yorkers which have increased due to the current recession.
EventItemMatterName: Examine how the City’s economic policies can be strengthened to address the disparate unemployment rate and joblessness of black New Yorkers.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Senate to pass S.2244 and the New York State Assembly to pass companion bill A.9989, which would create a rehabilitation program of civic service, education, and job training to assist non-violent felony offenders reintegrate successfully into society.
EventItemMatterName: Create a rehabilitation program of civic service, education, and job training to assist non-violent felony offenders reintegrate successfully into society. (S.2244/A.9989)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the enhanced 911 emergency telephone system surcharge.
EventItemMatterName: Enhanced 911 emergency telephone system surcharge.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to accepting Metropolitan Transportation Authority’s Access-A-Ride identification cards and reduced-fare MetroCards with additional official proof of address of New York City residency for the purpose of proving the identity and residency of applicants for New York City Disability Parking Permits.
EventItemMatterName: Accepting MTA’s Access-A-Ride identification cards and reduced-fare MetroCards with additional official proof of address of NYC residency.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to solid waste collections.
EventItemMatterName: Solid waste collections.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass legislation which would require the U.S. State Department to distribute to the City of New York withheld foreign aid funds equivalent to unpaid diplomatic parking fines owed to the City.
EventItemMatterName: U.S. State Department to distribute to NYC withheld foreign aid funds equivalent to unpaid diplomatic parking fines owed to the City.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Department of Homeless Services to refer individuals and families whose section 8 vouchers were revoked to the New York City Housing Authority for priority placement in public housing apartments.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the Dept of Homeless Services to refer individuals and families whose section 8 vouchers were revoked to the NYC Housing Authority for priority placement in public housing apartments.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the use of auxiliary power units in ambulances.
EventItemMatterName: Use of auxiliary power units in ambulances.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring protective devices for seniors and persons with a disability who reside in multiple dwellings.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring protective devices for seniors and disabled persons who reside in multiple dwellings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring owners to notify tenants of unsafe conditions of exterior walls of buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring owners to notify tenants of unsafe conditions of exterior walls of buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to establishing a survey division within the Landmarks Preservation Commission.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing a survey division within the Landmarks Preservation Commission.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring public parking garages to install pedestrian warning devices at parking garage exits.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring public parking garages to install pedestrian warning devices at parking garage exits.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to timely consideration of requests for evaluation by the Landmarks Preservation Commission.
EventItemMatterName: Timely consideration of requests for evaluation by the Landmarks Preservation Commission.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the establishment of a pilot program for the remediation of mold and vermin conditions in certain multiple dwellings.
EventItemMatterName: Establishment of a pilot program for the remediation of mold and vermin conditions in certain multiple dwellings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to enact A.9230/S.3326-A in relation to Mitchell-Lama and project-based Section 8 housing developments.
EventItemMatterName: Mitchell-Lama and project-based Section 8 housing developments. (A.9230/S.3326-A)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to amend Article 11 of the New York State Environmental Conservation Law to add Quaker Parrots to the list of "protected birds," which will oblige the City to take all possible steps to humanely relocate Quaker Parrots that have nested on city-owned properties that are slated for demolition or removal or where other projects require removal of the birds.
EventItemMatterName: Amend Article 11 of the NYS Environmental Conservation Law to add Quaker parrots to the list of “protected birds".

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to energy efficiency requirements for certain capital projects.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: A Resolution. in support of the Plaintiffs in the litigation captioned The United States of America v. The State of Arizona, Case No. CV 10-1413-PHX (SRB); in support of all branches of federal, state and local government using their power to oppose the Arizona law, including banning government employees from using public funds to travel to Arizona; and endorsing the Council's decision to file an amicus brief in support of the federal action at its discretion.
EventItemMatterName: Boycott of the State of Arizona in response to its anti-immigrant legislation.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring photographs to be included with certain notices of violation for parking violations.
